  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "rootLevel I understand is to do with the hierachicalLevel rendering. My issue as follows.\r\nI have an implementation of instant search on the home page. A hierarchicalMenu with two levels which aggregates the total number of results and links pointing to the respective aggregated results is present on the homepage. On this page, the instantsearch works as expected.\r\n i.e. If http://example.com is the home page, the aggregated results links are like http://example.com/q?=queryString which works fine. \r\nHowever, the hierarchicalMenu implemented from an inner page, say http://example.com/inner-page, the hierarchicalMenu links are now relative to this inner page like so, http://example.com/inner-page?q=queryString which obviously doesn’t give any results.\r\nIs there any way that from an inner page, the menu links are still relative to the home page.",
    "created_at": "2018-05-17T15:34:03Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2930#issuecomment-389909503",
    "id": 389909503,
